<title>USA: Monroc Inc takes $0.32 per shr Q3 charge.</title>
<headline>Monroc Inc takes $0.32 per shr Q3 charge.</headline>
<dateline>SALT LAKE CITY 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Building-materials group Monroc Inc said on Monday it would take a third-quarter charge of about $1.5 million, or $0.32 a share, and restructure its operations and finances.</p>
<p>Monroc said in a news release it would shut unprofitable operations in Utah and Wyoming and sell or dispose of obsolete facilities and equipment as part of the restructuring.</p>
<p>The non-recurring charges was also related to settling a two-year employment agreement with former chairman and chief executive Robert Parry, who retired in May 1996.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1713</p>
